# Run the project Locally

In this lecture we will use the `docker compose` which is installed as part of `docker`.

Just go to the directory of cloned repo and run `docker compose up`.

Video of the lecture is self explanatory.

1. Clone the repository
2. Run docker compose (Issue- No space left on device)
3. Modify volume to 30 gb
4. df -h
5. lsblk
6. sudo apt install cloud-guest-utils
7. sudo growpart /dev/xvda 1
8. lsblk
9. df-h
10. Update file system (sudo resize2fs /dev/xvda1)
11. df -h

Access the application internally (Update SG)
